That way no currency or NFTs could be transfered out without confirming on your hardware wallet but you could still gain access to holders sections of project websites using the hot wallet. @Ledger @MetaMask  is this possible? 4/4

My solution is hardware wallets should be able to link to/assign a single hot wallet and enable it to sign a subset of transactions, for example just read only messages for example to prove they own a specific NFT. 3/4

The problem with this is they can‚Äôt sign messages to enter holders sections of project‚Äôs sites or use services like collab land. Often they have to waste gas transferring to a hot wallet and back again to claim presale list or login somewhere.  2/4

I‚Äôve been thinking a bit about NFT security and hardware wallets. Many people, rightly, have a vault hardware wallet to store their collection and crypto but also have a policy of never connecting the hardware wallet to any website or dapp. 1/4
